Initial Planning – Note

This planning is defined at the end of the framing phase and remains unchanged thereafter.
The date must be specified.
Any subsequent updates must be reflected in the Updated Planning tab.


This document aims to align with the standards and guidelines provided by the Group.
As such, certain section titles and structures have been retained as defined by the Group, while being adapted and aligned with our internal methodology and practices.

This document serves as a reference framework for the project, ensuring consistency, traceability, and compliance with Group expectations, while allowing for pragmatic implementation at local level.

The documentation is reviewed on a quarterly basis. Feedback collected during the quarter is consolidated in a dedicated tracking document, which is used to assess required updates and improvements. This structured review process ensures that the documentation remains up to date, relevant, and aligned with evolving needs and standards.
